How the Robot Will Function
	•	 First-Time Interaction
	•	Robot Self-Introduction
The robot introduces itself and its purpose, sharing the Rainbow Diverse story to engage the child.
	•	Level 1 Engagement
The child begins with Level 1 (breathing exercise) guided by the robot.
	•	Feedback Check
After completing a level, the robot asks the child whether they want to move to the next level, repeat the current level, or stop interacting with the robot.
	•	Progression Through Levels
Children can choose to explore all five levels, progressing at their own pace.

	•	Subsequent Interactions (after the first three rounds of interactions, the robot will start with emotion detection)
	•	Emotion Detection
The robot detects the child’s facial expressions to assess mood.
	•	Adaptive Activity Selection
If happy: Robot offers body rhythm exercises or music imitation activities; the child can select which option to try.
If sad or stressed: Robot guides the child through the breathing exercise (Level 1) for emotional regulation.


	•	Feedback After Activity
Positive response: Robot introduces advanced activities such as Emotion-Music Mapping or Co-Creation Music.
Negative response: Robot checks if the child wants to switch exercises or take a short break.
	•	Exercise Adjustment
If the child chooses to switch, the robot presents alternative options from other levels, allowing the child to continue in a comfortable, engaging way.

